name: Starbucks Coffee
directions: The one on the lowest level in accessible, there are two more up on the top floor you can only get up to by stairs

name: Petsmart
directions: Back right corner of store
comment: Many LGBT employees, very open environment, store does not tolerate harassment

name: Trader Joe's
directions: Two unisex, single stall bathrooms in the back left of the building near the free samples.
comment: I've never had any problems here. They probably won't mess with you if you only plan to use the bathroom.

name: Michigan Union
directions: Third floor, directly off elevators.

name: University of Ottawa Peréz Building
directions: First floor in the small lobby. The door is directly across from the office door and is unmarked.
comment: Door is unmarked but is safe clean and locks

name: Fireside Books & Gifts
directions: all the way in the back, towards the left of the shop
comment: mon-fri 9:30 am-8:00 pm; sat 9:30-5; sun 10-4. no one will complain if you stop in to use the bathroom - it's always open during business hours - but it's a book shop and a friendly one, so there's plenty to look at and the owners have always been responsive to requests for anything you don't find in the store. there's also free coffee most of the time by the magazines.

name: University Guest House & Conference Center
directions: lobby level -- make a left once you come in from main lobby entrance. there are 2 unisex bathrooms down the hallway. ask front desk if any questions.

name: Rail City Market
directions: Stay to the left. Bathroom is in back room on left.
comment: As a courtesy, let the employees know where you are going, since it is in the back room. Everyone is welcome to use the bathroom at any time. There is a small single bathroom with a toilet and sink inside.

name: Artisan Kitchen
directions: Go into the dining area. It is through the doorway in the back, immediately on the left.

name: Rail City Market
directions: Stay to the left and go all the way back. Located in back room on left side.
comment: As a courtesy let an employee know you are using the bathroom, since it's in the back room. Everyone is welcome to use the bathroom at any time. Single small bathroom with toilet and sink inside. Not accessible due to one small step to get into the store.

name: Prosser Public Library
comment: Occasionally the bathrooms are locked and require you to ask for a key from the front desk, due to vandalism.

name: University of Essex Students' Union
directions: On the right of the SU gendered toilets.

name: Eden Bus Station
directions: At the end, near the gendered toilets. Single stall.

name: Brown House- Dominican University
directions: Back corner of the Brown House (art department)

name: Angelico Hall-Dominican University
directions: 3rd floor
comment: 2 stalls in a unisex bathroom

name: Angelico Hall-Dominican University
directions: 3rd floor
comment: 2 stalls in a unisex bathroom

name: Castro Country Club
directions: Bathroom is now opened by a buzzer behind the counter.  Effectively the same as asking for a key.
comment: Currently under construction (2/7/14)

name: Homeless Action Center
directions: all the way in the back. follow hall to end, then on left.
comment: Avail to all. 9-5 M-F. If the front door is locked during these times, knock and ask to use the bathroom.

name: Mount Saint Vincent University
directions: Seton Annex Main Floor

name: Edmonds Community College Brier Hall
directions: Single-occupant with internal stall, gender neutral bathroom in the first floor hallway near the stairs and security phone (phone is outside building) located at 47.816705,-122.327123 on Google Maps.
comment: Accessible to the public during business hours (7:00 am to around 8:00 pm, Mon-Fri).

name: Trader Joe's
directions: In the back of the store

name: Home Depot
directions: Go into home depot, down Aisle 5, straight to the back and it's right next to the men's room and drinking fountain.
comment: Use it all the time while working.

name: Top Pot
directions: To the right.
comment: Mostly for paying customers. But would be ok otherwise.

name: Philz Coffee
directions: Up the stairs, all the way to the back and to the far right
comment: There is a lift for wheel chairs but sometimes the back room can be pretty crowded

name: Vermont Thrush Restaurant
directions: Near the bar
comment: 2 small single stall unisex locking bathrooms. Very friendly staff.

name: Main Street Coffee and News
directions: towards the back down a small set of stairs
comment: These facilities are shared with the local LGBTQ youth center

name: PH
directions: All floors
comment: corporate

name: University of Denver Graduate School of Social Work
directions: Main floor has multi-stall gender-neutral bathroom and each floor has a single-stall gender neutral bathroom.

name: University of King's College
directions: There are several single stall, gender neutral bathrooms at King's - two on the second floor NAB on either side of the Wilson Room (opposite the Red Room), one outside of Prince Hall, one down the stairs outside the Wardy by the ATM machine. Any student will be happy to direct you further given any of these reference points!

name: UW Madison Sterling Hall
directions: the bathroom is located in the Gender and Women's Studies department of the university on the third floor of the building. The main entrance to the building is a staircase to the first floor, but just to the north of the main doors there is an accessible entryway into the basement, with access to an elevator from there.
comment: it's a university campus building, probably has security rules about being there for campus-related business

name: University of Wisconsin, Madison - Sterling Hall
directions: Third floor, by the elevators
comment: Door-less stalls (but I've never seen anyone else using the bathroom, so I wouldn't worry)

name: Vintage Tex
directions: The bathroom is in the public part of the store, down the hallway on the left.
comment: From the Owner: This is a small vintage clothing store that is usually not too busy. You don't need to buy anything.

name: King House
directions: When you enter through the main door, turn left.  Go all the way to the end and take the door on the left.
comment: I've included these loos under "a safe place".  They are gendered, but are small and not heavily used--unless a big event is taking place.  If you're at all comfortable in such a loo, I think you'll be OK here.

name: Supervalu
directions: Enter the main door of this shopping complex and go straight on back.  Easy to find.  This isn't a big place.
comment: I've included these loos under "a safe place".  They are gendered, but they're not heavily used.  So if you're at all comfortable in such a loo, I don't think you'll run into problems here.

name: Boyle Library
directions: Just inside the library entrance.  Take the door on the right just before you enter the library proper.
comment: No need to be a library user.  You can go right in.  Library hours may be a problem: 1-8 Tuesday and Thursday, 10-1 and 2-5 Wednesday, Friday and Saturday.

name: King House Café
directions: At the back.
comment: You may not need to be a paying customer.  It's a relaxed place.

name: Stone House Café
directions: Upstairs.
comment: You have to be a paying customer.

name: Black Sheep Cafe
directions: Directly to the right of the main entrance.
comment: Only open when there are events going on. Check availability at blacksheepspringfield.com

name: Richland Community College
directions: First floor, down C-South Hall behind the Art Room to the left.

name: Kohl's
directions: First floor, back by customer service

name: F.R.O.G.S.  Cantina
comment: I didn't ask but would assume paying customer is required

name: Women's Resources and Research Center
directions: On the first floor of North Hall
comment: Also a great place for resources for all marginalized genders!

name: Starbucks
directions: Starbucks is on the bottom floor of the building. Restroom is past the counter on the left.

name: Tropics
directions:
First floor Restaurant
Back
comment: Not Certian but its a bar Restaurant

name: Utah Pride Center
directions: All restrooms are Gender Neutral

name: Starbucks
directions: Private bathrooms

name: SF Citadel
directions: Go upstairs and walk towards the very back end of the space
comment:
Generally, you need to be there for either an event or a class. 

There's a staircase leading up tothe main space so it's not the most accessible.

Also, once there, you'll see two  restrooms but booth of them are unmarked and one of them contains a urinal. Anyone can go to either one.

name: University of Rochester, Wilson Commons
directions: In Wilson Commons building near Rush Rhees library. Two restrooms on the 3rd floor near Starbucks, both single stall and gender neutral.

name: The Hook-Up
directions: Enter around the back if you need to use the restrooms of this bar. There are two and there's never been a hassle for trans* people using a preferred bathroom.
comment: Enter through the backdoor if you're not already a bar customer.

name: Community Health Centers of Burlington
directions: Two on the first floor by dental check-in, one upstairs by medical check-in.

name: Hooligans
directions: Walk past the kitchen and counter. Take the next right.
comment: Be a paying customer or wait for it to be crowded.

name: Mother Fool's
directions: Towards the back. Single stall, unisex.
comment: You probably have to be a paying customer, but it's a super progressive/hippie spot so I wouldn't be surprised if they just let you go!

name: Barriques
directions: In the back of the shop.
comment: Supposed to be for paying customers, but you could go in the back door and enter the restroom and the only people that might notice are the folks roasting beans (it's a coffee shop/roastery) across the hall.

name: Collectivo Coffee
comment: Bathrooms are for customers but it's usually busy enough that you can slip in and use them without buying anything.

name: Graze
directions: On the main floor, away from the upstairs restrooms is a single unisex/family/accessible bathroom.
comment: For customer use only, but it's a great restaurant on the square.

name: ZtG (Center for transdisciplinary Gender Studies)
directions: first floor
comment: only open from Monday to Friday (8am-8pm)

name: Maynard Hall, The Ohio State University at Marion
directions: Door next to women's bathroom

name: Südblock
directions: first floor, next to the bar

name: Copenhagen Central Station
directions: København H train station.  Main floor, opposite side of building from the trains.
comment: Large, clean multi-stall gender-neutral pay restroom.  Common areas including sinks and waiting in line is mixed with all genders.  Costs 5 kroner to use.

name: St. David's Episcopal Church
directions: On the third floor, outside the sanctuary. The street entrance is on the second floor, so it is just one flight of stairs or there is an elevator.
comment: The church is open during the week and available for self-guided tour of the historic sanctuary. There is also a coffee shop and customers are welcome to use the restrooms. There are also many events open to the public.

name: Santos Manuel Student Union
directions: Ground floor, across from the atrium.

name: Redwood
directions: Bar.  Two gender-neutral single-stall restrooms.  One to the back left when you enter, one to the back right near the bar.

name: Red Onion
directions: In the back, on the right

name: Central Co-op
directions: Formerly known as "Madison Market".  Two gender-neutral restrooms in a small hallway past the fresh produce.

name: Raygun Lounge
directions: Get key at counter. Shared restroom with Black Coffee Co-op. Multiple-person gender-neutral restroom.

name: Black Coffee Co-op
directions: Get key at front desk.  Shared restroom with Raygun Lounge.  Multiple-person gender-neutral restroom.

name: Boston University School of Social Work
directions: First floor

name: University College, University of Toronto
directions: On the third floor of the F cloister wing (go into the quad and enter through the 'F' door).
comment: A bit hard to find but good to know about.

name: The Larkin Building, Trinity College, U of T
directions: by the sliding doors to enter the George Ignatieff Theatre.
comment: It's a university building, but open to everyone, closes around 8 or 9pm

name: Leroy
directions: Very first bathroom in the hall. It's marked "WC."

name: McNamara Alumni Center
directions: 1st floor, by the stairwell
comment: The building is open to the public

name: Portland Community College--Cascade Campus
directions:
Student Services Building, 3rd floor.
Jackson Hall, 2nd floor, end of East hallway (SE corner)
comment: People come from all over campus to use these lavatories, and little to no attention is paid.

name: Monopolatte
directions: Along the hallway to the back of the Cafe.
comment: The staff say "don't be opperssed by the signs on the doors". They are just their to meet legal requirements. The staff won't say anything if you pop in to look around then use then bathroom.

name: The Center OC
directions: Upstairs. Two single stall restrooms. One has a urinal; the other has no urinal.
comment: LGBT center, presumably safe space.

name: Berkeley Community Media
directions: Just go in the double doors where an open LED sign is blinking.

name: Main Street Books Monroe
directions: Through the exit door into the back room, on your left.

name: HyVee
directions: By the pharmacy.
comment: Single locking bathroom stall. They have no way of knowing if you are a paying customer.

name: Starbucks
directions: From the front, go to the left of the counter where it splits into two hallways.  Go to the hallway on the right and there will be two gender neutral, single stall restrooms there.  From the back, walk in and turn left once the narrow hallway ends.
comment: It's less sketchy if you buy something, but they probably won't notice, especially if you come in from the back.  I hang out there with friends and they don't care that not everyone buys something.

name: Crenshaw House
directions: Down the hall towards the back of the building (from the front entrance. I do not think the bathroom is accessible. There are some stairs to get into the front of the building.
comment: Crenshaw is the house for the department of Gender and Sexuality. The professors in the department are awesome and for the most part super trans positive. Probably should be a student, but they are usually super awesome anyway.

name: The Artful Dodger
directions: In the back
comment: It is a single-stall, accessible restroom.

name: Yale WLH classroom
directions: Near the elevator on the 1st and 2nd floors.
comment: Technically only Yalies & guests are allowed in to the building but no one pays attention.

name: Loyola University Chicago
directions: 1st floor of the Terry Student Center, right next to the elevators.
comment: May sometimes require student ID but seems to be open regularly.

name: Loyola University Chicago
directions: In the back of the Madonna Della Strada chapel, closest to the lake, there is a bathroom on each side.
comment: Sometimes space is reserved for private events/prayer. May require student ID.

name: Loyola University Chicago
directions: Coffey Hall - Room # 108
comment: May sometimes required student ID (unsure)

name: Loyola University Chicago
directions: Mundelein - several bathrooms. Room #s 156, 422, 717
comment: May sometimes required student ID (unsure)

name: Loyola University Chicago
directions: Room 005 - in the basement of Cuneo Hall, kind of caddy corner from the elevators.
comment: May sometimes required student ID (unsure)

name: Loyola University Chicago
directions: In the hallway adjacent to the food court (Damen Dining)

name: Michigan Technological University
directions: This is Wadsworth Hall and there is one handicapable unisex bathroom for every set of stall bathrooms in this building.
comment: You just have to go where people live and not where the dining hall is.

name: The Lakes Mall
directions: A gender-neutral family restroom near the food court and indoor playground.

name: Reed College
directions: 2 all-gender-inclusive restrooms on the lower floor of the Gray Campus Center, most easily accessed from the North side of the building
comment: campus is open to the public, but obviously after dark you can't get into buildings without a student swipe card or someone taking pity on you and letting you in
